
                                            MMC for Saftey Michael Sun says while they are grateful for more manpower as law enforcement officers, they won't be tolerating any corruption.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg  has welcomed over 200 graduates to its police department. MMC for Saftey Michael Sun  says while they are grateful for more manpower as law enforcement officers, they won't be tolerating any corruption. Sun says their deployment in the run-up to the festive season will help fight crime. “This will be a force multiplier in our policing. Powers have now been increased in JMPD. And this really will come in handy as the festive period approaches.”